page.title: 18Lt.Walsingham
page.content: It is a little village in North Norfolk.It's a very old village with a tremedous amount of history.Many years ago there used to be a priory.It has fallen into ruins and is now called the Abbey.Mr.and Mrs.Gurney live there.The Gurneys own the majority of both villages.Also there is a friary.The Wileys live there.They are not nearly as important as the Gurneys.I enjoy living in Walsingham.There are a great many half_timbered houses.These were built in the 1400's.Walsingham is famous for it's pilgrims.Thousands come at the same time.There is a peaceful river that runs through both villages.The railway came in 1850.It is now closed and its place taken by a narrow gauge private railway. by Donna Williamson Age 11.
